WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:10.840
Question: Having been to various International 
Forums and met many great leaders,

00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:16.560
where do you see the world heading,
for the better or the worst?

00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:19.300
Sadhguru: Let me correct that question a bit.

00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:22.180
Yes, I’ve been in international forums,

00:00:22.180 --> 00:00:24.440
met many leaders.

00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:32.560
You added “great” leaders (Few laugh).

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:38.300
So, many leaders – not always so great.

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:43.950
Yes, there are a few great leaders,
no question about that.

00:00:43.950 --> 00:00:49.680
Where is the world heading?

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:51.880
(Laughs)

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:54.560
There are many possibilities

00:00:54.560 --> 00:01:01.200
because we have capabilities and technologies,

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:05.740
which no other generation could ever dream of.

00:01:05.740 --> 00:01:10.240
Will our capabilities turn against us,

00:01:10.240 --> 00:01:14.767
or will they work for us is the big question.

00:01:14.767 --> 00:01:24.580
If all the human capabilities, which are so
hugely enhanced because of technology,

00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:28.040
everything that an individual human being could do

00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:31.800
has expanded manifold,

00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:34.920
in this enhanced state

00:01:34.920 --> 00:01:38.765
- and our numbers have increased tremendously.

00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:46.540
In the beginning of twentieth century,
we were just about 1.5 billion people,

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:50.680
today we are 7.3 billion people.

00:01:50.680 --> 00:02:01.480
The United Nations making predictions that by 2050, 
we will be 9.7 billion people.

00:02:01.480 --> 00:02:09.160
If all these people get educated,
get technologically empowered,

00:02:09.160 --> 00:02:17.900
9.7 billion people or nearly 10 billion people 
on this planet is for sure going to be a disaster.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:19.940
Yes.

00:02:19.940 --> 00:02:22.920
We can make arrangements and arrangements,

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:28.460
we can improve the arrangements,
we can make more energy-saving machines,

00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:32.600
we can recycle the shit (Laughter).

00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:34.680
Yes (Laughs).

00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:38.200
We can do all this,

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:49.700
but if we don’t come to our senses with human populations, there’s going to be…

00:02:49.700 --> 00:02:58.480
I want you to just imagine, how the world will be if the population almost goes up by fifty percent tomorrow.

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:05.420
Just imagine your town, how it will be if
fifty percent population increases tomorrow morning.

00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:10.380
Or in other words, no matter what we create,

00:03:10.380 --> 00:03:13.260
no matter how much we strive,

00:03:13.260 --> 00:03:15.400
whether…

00:03:15.400 --> 00:03:17.560
whatever we build,

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:19.860
everything is going to be insufficient

00:03:19.860 --> 00:03:22.900
because the planet is going to be insufficient.

00:03:22.900 --> 00:03:31.280
Of course, we are looking at planets which
could sustain life outside of this solar system.

00:03:31.280 --> 00:03:35.200
We’ve found two, three very promising planets,

00:03:35.200 --> 00:03:43.220
it’s just a little, you know,
not in the walking distance (Laughter) -

00:03:43.220 --> 00:03:47.481
a few thousand or a million light years away.

00:03:47.481 --> 00:03:52.056
Great planets, I believe.

00:03:52.056 --> 00:03:55.220
But this is the thing...

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:59.360
but nobody wants to address this issue.

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:02.980
Everybody wants to talk about cosmetic solutions,

00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:08.621
not address the basic problem
of expanding human population.

00:04:08.621 --> 00:04:16.040
I was in a conference and I said, “See, unless you (Laughs)…

00:04:16.040 --> 00:04:21.020
Unless you reduce the human footprint on the planet,

00:04:21.020 --> 00:04:25.460
there is no solution for anything.”

00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:30.680
Then they asked me a brilliant question,
“How do you reduce the human footprint?”

00:04:30.680 --> 00:04:36.720
I said, “You have to reduce the number of feet (Laughter).

00:04:36.720 --> 00:04:39.460
That’s the only way.” (Laughs)

00:04:39.460 --> 00:04:45.660
So right now,

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:55.800
it doesn’t matter what others think, all of you who are here and those of you who’re hanging out with me,

00:04:55.800 --> 00:05:02.180
we can take it upon ourselves that
we will not push the human population.

00:05:02.180 --> 00:05:06.300
You can have a dog.

00:05:06.300 --> 00:05:11.120
A husband and wife were having a debate –

00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:15.410
whether to have a child or not.

00:05:15.410 --> 00:05:20.920
The husband wanted a child, the wife hesitating because

00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:26.460
she will lose the shape of her body,
and you know (Laughter)…

00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:31.640
For a husband, having a baby is simple (Laughter).

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:35.280
But for the woman, it’s too many things involved.

00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:40.280
So, debate was going on and then they came
and the debate moved into an area

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:46.600
where, “Should we have a baby or should we get a dog” (Laughter)?

00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:50.140
Then they could not decide, they went to a counselor,

00:05:50.140 --> 00:05:53.060
they put their problem in front of him.

00:05:53.060 --> 00:06:01.246
So, he said, “You got to just make up your mind,
whether you want to ruin the carpets, or your life.”

00:06:01.246 --> 00:06:06.220
(Laughter/Applause)

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:12.500
I am not saying children are bad, they are wonderful, but

00:06:12.500 --> 00:06:16.340
it’s just too many.

00:06:16.340 --> 00:06:20.780
We as human beings, we are wonderful
but we are too many.

00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:26.760
We’re so many, that the insect population
is going down (Laughter).

00:06:26.760 --> 00:06:28.600
No, no, it’s not a joke, it’s very…

00:06:28.600 --> 00:06:34.240
it’s very threatening. If the insect population disappears, the planet will be destroyed.

00:06:34.240 --> 00:06:34.940
Yes.

00:06:34.940 --> 00:06:37.940
The worms disappear, the planet will be destroyed.

00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:46.300
If you and me disappear, planet will flourish
(Laughter/Applause).

00:06:46.300 --> 00:06:52.860
So, leave the leaders alone,
because in every conference that you meet,

00:06:52.860 --> 00:06:59.740
very cosmetic solutions are being talked about –
how to adjust the market place,

00:06:59.740 --> 00:07:01.140
okay (Laughs)?

00:07:01.140 --> 00:07:03.180
How to do this, how to do that.

00:07:03.180 --> 00:07:06.920
I… On immediate scale, yes, those things are necessary.

00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:10.140
But you’re talking about what is the future of this world.

00:07:10.140 --> 00:07:14.400
If that is so, if we want a future for this world,

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:19.700
if we want our children and their
children to live well on this planet,

00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:24.360
the only way is to bring down human population.

00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:27.860
Not by doing some horrible acts,

00:07:27.860 --> 00:07:34.180
but if we have - see, our life expectancy has improved.

00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:37.680
This means we have taken death into our hands.

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:39.940
When we take death into our hands,

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:48.900
it is our business to take birth also into our hands, 
isn't it (Applause)?

00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:54.920
If we convince the population of this one thing,

00:07:54.920 --> 00:08:01.520
future is very bright, because tomorrow morning
the sun will come up, what’s the problem (Laughs)?

